The paper deals with the problem of finding a quasi-optimal number of coded packets to multicast to a set of independent wireless receivers suffering different channel conditions. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), network engineering (cs.NE), control systems (cs.SY), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
